<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation in Spain</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-21"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister for foreign affairs says Dupuy’s note concerning your No. 408
                            received to-day was prior special examination. Minister said he was
                            disposed to grant at once to consuls of the United States in Cuba all
                            rights guaranteed to German consul under the treaty of 1870.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>